{"article_id":"PpAF65bu7xBCYBNW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A failure","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to raise the debt limit","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"will have 'catastrophic ' effects ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Lew warns .","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"| REUTERS","depth":2},{"id":5,"text":"Lew takes on debt deniers","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Treasury Secretary Jack Lew warned Congress on Thursday","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"that lawmakers","depth":12},{"id":8,"text":"who have cast doubt on the impact of a government default","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"are gravely mistaken","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"and are putting the U.S. economy at risk .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Treasury has said","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that the government will run out of its ability","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"to borrow money","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"starting on Oct. 17","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"and will soon after not be able to pay all the government ' s bills on time and in full .","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"Treasury officials , business leaders and most economists have said","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that failing to raise the debt ceiling could cause havoc in financial markets ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"which rely on U.S. debt securities ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"and hurt the economy .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"But in recent days some Republicans have questioned","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"how bad the situation would be","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and others , as well as some market analysts , have suggested","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"there is more time","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"to negotiate over a debt limit hike","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"than Treasury has stated .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"\" It is irresponsible and reckless to insist","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that we experience a forced default","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"to learn how bad it is , \"","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Lew told the Senate Finance Committee .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"\" If anything at all is learned from the shutdown ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"it will convince the deniers","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"- or a majority","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"who can work their will -","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"to avoid putting the entire economy at risk in the name of an ideological fight . \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Republicans have been critical of Lew ,","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"he is trying to scare financial markets","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"to get Congress to boost the debt ceiling","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"without attaching a budget deal or changes to the president ' s health care law to the legislation .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"Sen. Orrin Hatch","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"( R-Utah )","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"told Lew at Thursday ' s hearing","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"that he and President Barack Obama have been causing needless panic with suggestions","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that Social Security recipients and disabled workers would see deep cuts","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"without an increase in the debt limit","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"while failing to explain how the government could manage a default .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"\" It is disconcerting that administration officials are soundings alarms of emerging risks to financial stability","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"arising from the debt limit impasse , \"","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"the committee ' s top Republican said .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"\" The Financial Stability Oversight Council... has been silent","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and refused to tell the American people how it would respond to these risks . \"","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Financial markets on Thursday were more interested in reports","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"that there is growing interest behind-the-scenes in Congress","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"for passing a short-term debt ceiling increase","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"than they were in the public sparring at the hearing .","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up more than 180 points in early morning trading .","depth":4},{"id":57,"text":"Speaking on Capitol Hill on the 10th day of the government shutdown ,","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"Lew took aim at the idea","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"that the Treasury Department can \" prioritize \" payments","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"so that bondholders can be paid first ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"avoiding a technical default ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"even if payments to other government creditors , such as Social Security recipients or contractors , are delayed .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"He did not , however , rule out","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"this course could be taken","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"if the debt ceiling is not raised","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"but did not provide details of how Treasury would try to manage a default .","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"At the urging of Senate Finance Committee Chairman Max Baucus","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"( D-Mont . ) ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Lew said","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"there are legal and technical questions","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"about whether and how Treasury could choose what bills","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to pay .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"\" The legal issues are many .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"I do not know","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"how you would make the decisions , \"","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Lew said .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"\" This system was not designed","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"to be turned off selectively .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"Anyone","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"who thinks","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"it can be done","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"just doesn ' t know the architecture of our payment system . \"","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Lew also questioned","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"what meaningful difference there is between whether bondholders are paid","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"if other creditors are not .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"prioritization is default by another name , \"","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Lew said.","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"\" It is just saying","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"we will default on some subset of our obligations . \"","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"A failure","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"to raise the debt limit","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"will have \" deeply damaging \" and \" catastrophic \" effects on the economy ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"he added .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Under questioning from Hatch , Lew declined to say","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"specifically how large of a debt limit increase the administration wants ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"telling the committee","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"the president will sign any bill","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"that avoids default","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"and does not contain other policy provisions .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"\" The longest","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Congress is prepared to extend it for","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"is the best , \"","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"he said .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":209,"left":109,"right":208,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":109,"left":108,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":107,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":106,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":106,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":160,"right":207,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":155,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":5,"right":154,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":137,"right":153,"relation":"ela